
### 1. Find the Largest Element in an Array

**Problem:** Given an array, find the maximum element.

```java
class LargestElement {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {3, 5, 1, 9, 2};
        int max = arr[0];

        for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] > max) {
                max = arr[i];
            }
        }
        System.out.println("Largest element: " + max);
    }
}
```

---

### 2. Find the Smallest Element in an Array

**Problem:** Given an array, find the minimum element.

```java
class SmallestElement {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {8, 4, 6, 2, 9};
        int min = arr[0];

        for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] < min) {
                min = arr[i];
            }
        }
        System.out.println("Smallest element: " + min);
    }
}
```

---

### 3. Reverse an Array

**Problem:** Reverse the given array.

```java
class ReverseArray {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
        int left = 0, right = arr.length - 1;

        while (left < right) {
            int temp = arr[left];
            arr[left] = arr[right];
            arr[right] = temp;
            left++;
            right--;
        }

        for (int num : arr) {
            System.out.print(num + " ");
        }
    }
}
```

---

### 4. Check if Array is Sorted

**Problem:** Check whether the array is sorted in ascending order.

```java
class CheckSorted {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
        boolean isSorted = true;

        for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] < arr[i - 1]) {
                isSorted = false;
                break;
            }
        }
        System.out.println("Is array sorted? " + isSorted);
    }
}
```

---

### 5. Sum of All Elements in an Array

**Problem:** Calculate the sum of elements in an array.

```java
class SumOfArray {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {2, 4, 6, 8};
        int sum = 0;

        for (int num : arr) {
            sum += num;
        }
        System.out.println("Sum of array: " + sum);
    }
}
```

---

### 6. Linear Search in an Array

**Problem:** Search for a key element using linear search.

```java
class LinearSearch {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {5, 3, 7, 1, 9};
        int key = 7;
        int index = -1;

        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] == key) {
                index = i;
                break;
            }
        }

        if (index != -1)
            System.out.println("Element found at index: " + index);
        else
            System.out.println("Element not found");
    }
}
```

---

### 7. Count Even and Odd Numbers in an Array

**Problem:** Count how many even and odd numbers are present.

```java
class EvenOddCount {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6};
        int even = 0, odd = 0;

        for (int num : arr) {
            if (num % 2 == 0)
                even++;
            else
                odd++;
        }
        System.out.println("Even count: " + even);
        System.out.println("Odd count: " + odd);
    }
}
```

